import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, estimator=lambda x: sum(x)/len(x))
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average stock price of each company?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    if len(data.symbol.unique()) > 20:
        sns.boxplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, showfliers=False)
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        sns.boxplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, showfliers=False)
        plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the volatility of stock prices for each company?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
